Visited the location for the first time today. While tickets were free online, brunch and Mimosas were $70 per guest. When asked about seating, my friends and I were given the run-around from the host and bartenders. When finally seated, the manager came and rudely stated "A group has brought this table, you will need to move". When we were seated the bartender who seated us explained that the table was a community table and other parties may possibly be seated with us. I don't appreciate that the messages did not align and the poor manner in which we were addressed by the manager. It's not what she said, but the way in which she said it.  Additionally,  we met a group who had purchased Mimosas but were about to leave. They expressed that they were unable to finish their picture and left it on our table. The bartender rushed to our table, confiscated our drinks, and took the Mimosa picture, as well. AGAIN, the issue is not that she took the drinks, but she failed to have a reasonable conversation with us (patrons who spent over $230) about their policy on sharing Mimosas. She was extremely rude and unprofessional. The customer service was subpar and I won't be patronizing this establishment again.

I decided to opt out of the mimosas cause i wasn't about to spend over $80 for brunch!  I am only giving two stars because the food is tasteless, the customer service was horrible.. we had a girlfriend that is vegan and we ask the manager if we could get her a plate of kale salad with fruits but she refused and told us she will have to pay full price for the brunch, mind you she ordered the $25 mimosas so its not like she was just there not spending money.  Definitely wouldn't come back for brunch! The only thing this place is good for is if you want to come dance and have a great time!

Last week Monday my friend sent me a Eventbrite link to the coming Day Party on Sunday, Memorial Day Weekend, asking Me if i wanted to go. I said sure and registered for my free ticket which is a limited time offer. Fast forward to Sunday, I get to the front of the line and they were no longer honoring there Event brite promotion even though I was there before the time. They then switched it from 6pm to a 5pm cut off. Several others decided not to go in because of  this and the fact that they now charged a $20 entry. Very misleading promotion, the security act as though they don't know what's going on but collect the cover from anyone who doesn't require explaination. Then they yelled at a young man for inquiring. I still decided to pay and go inside as it was for celebrating a friend birthday. I was hope to pay for at least a good time. Upon entry you see the illusion of the packed house is mostly due to the lack of space and positioning of ropes inside. Great marketing but bad for for paid customers. The first DO they had was terrible  switching song late or too fast. Transition between track was terrible. The second DO got alot better , way better music. A few NFL stars came through though ( went to my HS and college) so it was to see old acquaintances. But I wouldn't recommend  unless You are into paying for free promoted events with limited space and limited fun

I came here on a Saturday night to celebrate a friends birthday.  I'll start off with the good: this place has a very nice and "upscale" ambience. They have a lot of tables available for bottle service, but I honestly think they have too many tables.  Now for the bad: the business model is very scummy and everything tends to be expensive. I paid $13 for a simple mixed drink in a 8 oz cup and $9 for a corona extra. I learned that they automatically include the tip, so I didn't even both tipping. Also, the crowd seemed sketchy.  The last straw was when someone attempted to force me to "tip" to use the restroom. When I went, there was no one in the restroom, not even an attendant. Yet, after I left, a sketchy person attempted to shake me down for a "tip" to use the restroom. I initially brushed him off and went my merry way. That person then convinced a large bouncer to intimidate me into paying the "tip". Normally, I wouldn't have any problem paying the "tip" if an attendant helped me out, but I had my own reasons to leave the bar at that time. I left the bar without tipping and I will never return again.  Overall, this bar is very sketchy for their tipping practices and for the atmosphere.

Avoid this establishment at all cost unless you enjoy your food not coming out after 1.5 hours of waiting and a female waitress wearing a singlet with her booty cheeks hanging out while handling your food and drinks. Moreover, our party was the first to sit in this establishment and place our orders. However it took at least 45 minutes for some of the plates to come out and one of the plates had to be sent back three times because they kept placing an item onbthe plate that the customer was allergic to, and they were told that.  Confusingly, half of the meals were lost between the time the orders were placed and somewhere in the kitchen.  As a result, four of us had to cancel our orders after waiting for them to come out for over a 1.5 hours of waiting.  Moreover, we had a dirty glass that had a lip stick mark on the rim of the glass that we were expected to drink out of. My cup of coffee was inedible, it tasted like liquid cool, I had to ask for cream and one of the servers took 10 minutes to bring the heavy cream to me. When he came back, my coffee was ice cold and he had a very unhappy look on his face. Perhaps, he has the condition of  "RBF", I don't know; but it was very unappealing and disrespectful! I had to send the coffee back and have it removed from my bill. Not to mention,  we observed other tables be seated, eatting their food and leave without our meals even being cooked.  I felt bad for the waitress because it was likely the kitchen's fault but this was unacceptable. **UPDATE** Apparently, on Thursday nights, The Gryphon has amazing live bands performing. Add it to the list.  Awesome happy hour experience. Half-off raw bar, wine and cocktails. The oysters and clams were among the freshest I've had in DC, beating out some of the raw bar-bragging places. Sitting outside on a warm Wednesday, it felt... less DC. I'll be going here often. Let me just say that the experience i encountered at this place was unique, however not in any good way. Me and my companions were basically forced out of our table before we were done eating and drinking. Waitress was nice but floor manager has the worst people skills i have encountered thus far. We were still buying drinks and wanted to order desert and our bill was $360 at that time and even donated $60 to their charity event they had going on that night, and we were forced out because they had another party they wanted to sit down, and according to the floor manager the owner was present and well aware of what she was doing, so if you wanna leave few hundred dollars to an establishment that can care less about you go on, but none of us would ever go there, i wish google had negative star because they would receive all 5 of them with a minus in front.

If you like to eat sea creatures by the truckload this is prob your place...if you would like even the semblance of friendly and attentive service, you will  be sorely disappointed. Their "half price" (almost) everything includes all drinks and the raw bar.  That really is the best deal in Dupont.  The space is classic with lots of wood and brass with some outside tables on those nice days, with a full open front that can let in a nice breeze (as well as the sounds of the busy street).  The half price shrimp cocktail at $5 is a steal, and comes inventively prepared on a bed of tangy cocktail sauce topped with delicious lemon zest.  The clams were too fishy and tough--all 3 people at the table agreed, but it could have been a rough batch.  Drinks came at a glacial pace, and once happy hour was over, servers disappeared.  Gryphon is not quite ready for prime time.
